        progesterone, ovaries
    b.
        i.
            Plants' stems grow towards the direction of light. More specifically, plants grow away from darkness. Since light exposure is required for photosynthesis, and plants grow towards light, this increases their light exposure, allowing them to photosynthesis more and have more energy.

            Roots grow away from light. The ground is darkest, so this means roots grow deep into the ground and cannot accidentally grow upwards or something. This lets the plant access more sources of water and mineral in the ground which may be buried deeper, and also anchors the plant into the ground so it is not easily knocked over.
        ii.
            Flowering in plants may be stimulated by the number of hours of daylight rather than by temperature because temperatures may vary drastically in relatively small areas and vary drastically over the course of a day, so temperature is not a good indicator of what time of year it is. In addition, mechanisms for detecting temperature may not already be present, whereas light is already a vital part of plants' life and detected by shoots and roots.
9.
    a.
        The larvae of the moth causes a reduction in the yield of the maize crop because it eats the leaves of the maize plants, lowering the amount they can photosynthesize and hence the amount of maize generated, as the desirable parts of a maize plant are food storage organs.
    b?
        One advantage of biological control rather than chemical pesticides is that chemical pesticides may leach into the environment and kill other related or beneficial animals even far away, whereas biological control will not leach into the environment and any negative effects will be localised.
        Another advantage of biological control rather than chemical pesticides is that pests cannot become resistant to a predator species.
        Another advantage of biological control is that pesticides will bioaccumulate whereas biological control will not. Hence, biological control will be less disruptive to the ecosystem.
    c.
        i.
            The number of wasps increases roughly as the number of moths increases and decreases as the number of moths decrease, but slightly delayed. This is likely because as the amount of moths increases, there are more hosts for the parasitic wasps to occupy, so their numbers increase. As the amount of wasps increase, the moths are killed off, so there are less hosts for the wasps to occupy, so the amount of wasps decrease. However, the amoutn of wasps is offset likely because it takes some time for the population to respond to more/less hosts.

            This could also be periodic because as moths reproduce, larvae are generated, which the wasps can infest, and as the larvae die/mature the amount of larvae drop and the amout of wasps drop too as they have nothing to occupy.

            The peak amounts of moths and wasps are decreasing throughout. This indicates that this biological control method is working, and that less and less moths are reproducing each season. This is likely because less moth larvae make it to adulthood as a result of the wasps.
        ii.

            2150 - 850 = 1300
        iii.
            Some maize farmers might not choose to use biological control to control the moth because pesticide is likely more efficient at controlling the moths (takes less time), and because introducing a parasitic organism not already existing likely/often means introducing an invasive species, which can be detrimental to the ecosystem.
10.
    Take two identical glasshouses with genetically identical crops planted in them. In one of the glasshouses, increase the temperature by 3 degrees celcius.
    After 6 months, or whatever the average harvesting time is for that crop, harvest the crop, and measure the weight and volume of the desired parts of the harvest for each glasshouse. Ensure that during this process oxygen content, humidity, light exposure etc are kept the same. This can be done by putting them near each other and ensuring the same settings are used on their climate control systems.

    Repeat three times.